Trying the solution $a = 2, b = 1$ of the first equation, the second one reduces to $6\alpha + 16\beta = 16 \equiv 3\alpha + 8\beta = 7$, which has a solution $\alpha = -3, \beta = 2$. In conclusion, $3 \cdot (-8, -3) + 5 \cdot (8, -3) + 2 \cdot (3, 8) + 1 \cdot (-3, 8) = (19, 0)$. All we have to do is to make these moves in the right order, so that we keep within the boundaries. This way one can find the path

$$
\begin{array}{l} 
(0,0) \to (3,8) \to (11,5) \to (19,2) \to (16,10) \to (8,7) \\ 
